## Summary

**Changed**: `scripts/task_verification_gate.py` (+25 lines)

**What changed**:
1. Added `git_diff_summary(repo)` helper (lines 64-70) that collects staged, unstaged, and untracked files as three separate lists via `git diff --cached --name-only`, `git diff --name-only`, and `git ls-files --others --exclude-standard`.

2. Added `"diff_summary"` key to the `verify()` return dict (line 111), populated by the new helper. This is additive — no existing logic or "ok"/"reason" behavior was changed.

3. Added a self-test (lines 152-166) that creates staged, unstaged, and untracked files in a temp repo and asserts the `diff_summary` correctly categorizes each.

**Why this matters**: Previously, a reverted-no-edit task only produced the reason `"task produced no git-visible file changes"`, which collapsed two very different failure modes: (a) the agent never touched any file, vs (b) the agent made changes but they were reverted before verification. The new `diff_summary` field lets downstream consumers (dashboard, log_feedback) distinguish these cases by checking whether staged/unstaged/untracked lists are empty or non-empty at verification time.

**Verification**: `python3 scripts/task_verification_gate.py --test` — all self-tests passed, including the new diff_summary assertions.

